From: stuff overlay maintainer
Subject: pygwy: always use the bundled pygtk-embed at build time

gwyddion ships a self-contained pygtk-embed under modules/pygwy/
(headers byte-identical to upstream pygtk-2.0; codegen identical
modulo shebangs and two aux scripts gwyddion doesn't use). The
configure block first probes for system pygtk-2.0 via pkg-config
and only falls back to the bundle when missing.

In this overlay system pygtk:2 is being phased out together with
the rest of the py2 helper cluster (sk1 was the only other
consumer and was dropped 2026-04-24). Forcing the bundled path
removes the incidental pkg-config dependency so the gwyddion
build no longer needs dev-python/pygtk and dev-python/pygobject:2
to be installed.

The bundled fallback is functionally complete for pygwy: its
codegen is what pygwy needs at build time, the resulting pygwy.so
links neither libpyglib nor libpygobject (verified via nm -D /
ldd against an unpatched build), and runtime resolution of the
GObject helpers happens via gwyddion's own static glue and the
embedded CPython interpreter.

--- a/configure.ac
+++ b/configure.ac
@@ -283,24 +283,20 @@
 fi

 if test "x$enable_pygwy" != xno; then
-  PKG_CHECK_MODULES(PYGTK,[pygtk-2.0 >= 2.10.0],[],
-                    [embed_pygtk=yes; pygwy_warn=" (embedded pygtk2)"])
-  if test "x$embed_pygtk" = xno; then
-    if test "x$PYGTK_CODEGENDIR" = 'x'; then
-      PYGTK_CODEGENDIR=`$PKG_CONFIG --variable=codegendir pygtk-2.0`
-    fi
-  else
-    # Some silly OSes want to remove pygtk2.  We can build pygwy without
-    # requiring the pygtk/pygobject codegen stuff to be installed.  We still
-    # require the runtime packages.  These will be more difficult to embed.
+  # stuff overlay: always use the bundled pygtk-embed instead of
+  # probing for system pygtk via pkg-config.  System pygtk:2 is
+  # being phased out in this overlay (sk1 was its other consumer
+  # and got dropped 2026-04-24) and the bundled tree is
+  # functionally complete for pygwy's build needs.
+  embed_pygtk=yes
+  pygwy_warn=" (embedded pygtk2)"

-    # The local sub directory with codegen.
-    PYGTK_CODEGENDIR=pygtk-embed/codegen
-    # The pygtk flags are reall just the GTK+ flags, except the -I for
-    # pygobject.h.  But we know where we have it when embedding.
-    PYGTK_CFLAGS="$GTK_CFLAGS -Ipygtk-embed/include/pygtk-2.0"
-    PYGTK_LIBS="$GTK_LIBS"
-  fi
+  # The local sub directory with codegen.
+  PYGTK_CODEGENDIR=pygtk-embed/codegen
+  # The pygtk flags are really just the GTK+ flags, except the -I for
+  # pygobject.h.  But we know where we have it when embedding.
+  PYGTK_CFLAGS="$GTK_CFLAGS -Ipygtk-embed/include/pygtk-2.0"
+  PYGTK_LIBS="$GTK_LIBS"
   AC_SUBST(PYGTK_CFLAGS)
   AC_SUBST(PYGTK_LIBS)
   AC_SUBST(PYGTK_CODEGENDIR)
